Our client is looking to fill a vacancy within their IT Applications team.
This is an operational position wiith a focus on Quintiq applications and will
provide exceptional & timely support to users.

** Client Details **

Our client is a leading international meat packing company based in the United
Kingdom. It specialises in the packing and supply of meat products to major
retailers across Europe and Australia, operating state-of-the-art facilities
and focusing on delivering high-quality, innovative, and sustainable meat
solutions.

** Description **

The primary responsibilities will include:

  * Offer prompt and precise technical assistance to Quintiq application users. 
  * Identify and resolve various technical issues, encompassing software glitches, configuration challenges, and user mistakes. 
  * Record and escalate intricate issues to development and implementation teams. 
  * Create and manage knowledge base articles and other user guides. 
  * Provide fundamental user training and address inquiries regarding Quintiq features. 
  * Keep abreast of the most recent Quintiq releases and enhancements, and how these translate to business benefits 
  * Work closely with internal and external partners to streamline issue resolution. 
  * Engage in ongoing improvement endeavours to elevate support procedures and user satisfaction 

** Profile **

The successful candidate will have the following desirable factors:

  * Experience using Quintiq applications or similar supply chain and manufacturing planning software 
  * Minimum 2 Years experience in a similar application support role 
  * Experience with SAP and other ERP Systems 
  * Knowledge of planning processes in manufacturing, including production planning, scheduling, and inventory management 
  * A high level of technical and drive to address application issues without direction 
  * An analytic mindset that will constantly look at streamlining processes and continuous opportunities for improvement 
  * The ability to build and maintain relationships with cross-functional teams 
  * The ability to change mindsets relating to Qunitiq use & the need for best practise security measures 

** Job Offer **

Our client is offering:

  * Ability to based in either Brisbane or Melbourne 
  * Above market salary banding 
  * The opportunity to work with a market leading, international company & access to their state of the art facilities. Our client is known for their commitment to innovation, providing employees with the chance to work with cutting-edge technologies and processes 
  * Hybrid working environment and the chance to WFH multiple days per week 
  * Opportunities for employee growth and development, offering various training programs, advancement opportunities, and support for career progression. 

